text: Wendell Mosley (1932 – December 31, 1989) was an American football player and coach. He served as the head football coach at Texas Southern University from 1976 to 1978, compiling a record of 11–20–2. ==Head coaching record== ==References== Category:1932 births Category:1989 deaths Category:Oklahoma Sooners football coaches Category:Texas Southern Tigers football coaches Category:High school football coaches in Oklahoma Category:Deaths from cancer in Texas
